com.sun.tools.visualvm.tools.jvmstat
Class JvmstatModel

java.lang.Object
  com.sun.tools.visualvm.core.model.Model
      com.sun.tools.visualvm.tools.jvmstat.JvmstatModel

public abstract class JvmstatModel
extends Model

This class uses Jvmstat technology (http://java.sun.com/performance/jvmstat/) to obtatin various information from JVM. Note that Jvmstat is available in JDK 1.4.2 and up. It is also available for remote Java applications if jstatd daemon (http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/tooldocs/share/jstatd.html) is running on remote host.

Author:
Tomas Hurka

Method Detail

findByName

public abstract String findByName(String name)
Find a named counter exported via Jvmstat. This method will look for the named counter exported via Jvmstat. If a counter with a given name exists, a string value of such counter is returned. Otherwise, the method returns null.

Parameters:
name - the name of the counter to find.
Returns:
the string value of the counter, or null if the named counter doesn't exist.

findMonitoredValueByName

public abstract MonitoredValue findMonitoredValueByName(String name)
Find a named counter exported via Jvmstat. This method will look for the named counter exported via Jvmstat. If a counter with a given name exists, a MonitoredValue interface to that counter will be return. Otherwise, the method returns null.

Parameters:
name - the name of the counter to find.
Returns:
the MonitoredValue that can be used to monitor the the named counter, or null if the named counter doesn't exist.

findByPattern

public abstract List<String> findByPattern(String pattern)
Find a list of the named counters exported via Jvmstat. This method will look for the named counters with names matching the given pattern. This method returns a List of string values of the counters such that the name of each counter matches the given pattern.

Parameters:
pattern - a string containing a pattern as described in Pattern.
Returns:
a List of string values of the matching counters.

findMonitoredValueByPattern

public abstract List<MonitoredValue> findMonitoredValueByPattern(String pattern)
Find a list of the named counters exported via Jvmstat. This method will look for the named counters with names matching the given pattern. This method returns a List of MonitoredValue of the counters such that the name of each counter matches the given pattern.

Parameters:
pattern - a string containing a pattern as described in Pattern.
Returns:
a List of MonitoredValue of the matching counters.
